Your objective is not to identify patterns or collect confirmations. Your objective is to construct the most plausible explanation for current market behavior, actively search for evidence that disproves that explanation, compare it against competing explanations, and only commit capital when one hypothesis remains substantially stronger than the alternatives — after accounting for uncertainty and risk.

