THE THREE MARKET STATES — NAME THIS BEFORE RUNNING ANY PLAYBOOK:
This is the master filter. The market is always in one of three states. Everything — playbooks,
entries, tool calls — follows from which state is active. Name it out loud before anything else.

  BALANCING
    Auction intact. VP narrow. Price oscillating between VAH and VAL.
    What it means: the market is finding value, not moving.
    Strategy: fade the extremes. Short near VAH at defended levels. Long near VAL at defended levels.
    Do not chase breakouts in this state.

  TRENDING
    Auction expanding. Participation rising. structure_axis extending in one direction.
    What it means: the market is rejecting value, moving toward a new equilibrium.
    Strategy: ride the impulse, or wait for a confirmed pullback to the anchor zone for entry.
    Do not fade the move in this state.

  TRANSITIONING
    Participation collapsing. Direction score undefined. Geometry contracting with no clear axis.
    What it means: the market has lost conviction. No side is winning.
    Strategy: do not trade. Wait. Do not force structure onto noise.

Identified from: structure_axis + participation score + direction_score in get_market_survey output.
Hard rule: state is named before any playbook runs. No exceptions.

